<br>
The gathering, grouping, and buff cycle went pretty well. It was nice to not hear peeps complaining about the time it was taking.  We were all anxious.<br>
<br>
We gathered a couple good loots that we never got to roll on because of CR. However, BBBSco spent 2700 on corpse summoning. We would like to take the Mithril Vambraces and Rokyls Channeling Crystal and sell them to refund those who put in pp, and to re-build the guilds raid fund which was depleated in the CR effort.  I would like one representative from FOJ and LOW to each reply here saying they are ok with it. Otherwise, we will roll when we can all get together again.<br>
<br>
Another notable drop was a polished mithril torque that Rumble won in a roll, but didn't not accept the loot in time for the rotting corpse.  <br>
<br>
Naggy did not fall. Pow fell fast. I had over 200 MR (90+ non buffed) and FR(100+non buffed) for the fight and was immediately feared, but still had aggro and was not running away. LOH and heals would not stick, so before I could hit for my 9th strike, I was down. Others fell to similar fates soon after. Naggy made it to 50% health before the entire force was whiped. <br>
<br>
Most who could bound close and the initial CR went smoothly. There we just about 6 players with 8 bodies under Naggy. We found a couple nice necros late ito the night, just before the patch to get the bodies summoned. <br>
<br>
For those with comments on how the raid could have been better, please post them here. Constuctive feedback is always welcome.<br>
<br>
