<br>
One of the problems is we cannot rely on that new item link. Aruga can not use the new UI and had no clue in hell what he was rolling on till after the fact. I am sure there are others who cannot or do not use it either.<br>
<br>
I think if something is no drop and there is a minute left on the timer then maybe the raid lead takes a wild stab and picks someone who seems to come to raids a lot and could actually use the item. Playing favorites maybe, but that sucked that thing rotted, and it sucked a rogue was gonna loot it.<br>
<br>
As far as naggy: I have read more than once that Naggy is a lot harder since they made the resist changes. All we can do there is up our resists. <br>
<br>
I had a big problem last night with the fact that Impatience ruled the raid. We need to be fast moving yes, but there was too much impatience. If we are going to start leaving folks behind for the sake of the raid then I am not going to be raiding anymore, sorry.<br>
<br>
Also as far as the who map thing goes. It is wise to check the atlas's on www.eqatlas.com. But if one more person says the phrase &quot;get a map&quot; I am gonna lose it. My printer  is down, some people don't have printers and I think it is bordering on loserville to head to kinkos to print out a map everytime we raid. Whatever happened to helping your guildmates out? <p><center>
<a href="http://groups.msn.com/BBSCO/_whatsnew.msnw"><img src=http://coello.com/gnipgnop/ggpp4.jpg></a>
</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub47.ezboard.com/bblackburrowstoutco13800.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sanmaren>Sanmaren</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#330000>(9/27/02 6:26:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub47.ezboard.com/fblackburrowstoutco13800frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Naggy Results</span><hr size=1> Here's my two coppers worth:<br>
<br>
1.  LoW is discussing your request that items obtained during the raid be used to pay for the corpse summonses.  Personally, I have no problem with that; a guild ambassador should be contacting you (hopefully today) with our reply.<br>
<br>
2.  I was frustrated that I couldn't do much healing, as people were falling too fast.  I stayed in the prep room during the fight; should I have moved in closer so I could heal as needed?  When I did try to heal, people were &quot;out of range&quot;.  I ultimately camped out (when told to do so) and returned once it was safe.<br>
<br>
3.  How many level 52s were on the raid?  I've heard that level is a significant factor in determining whether Fear sticks.  Can anyone confirm this?  If this is true, then those in their 40s would have a much higher chance of being feared even with 200+ MR.<br>
<br>
4.  What happened in that earlier encounter with the boss giant?  A number of people (including myself) were killed.  Was that room trained on us by someone outside the raid?<br>
<br>
5.  I agree with Gnipgnop in that a better effort should be made to ensure that NO DROP items don't rot.  Yes, it might mean that some people won't get a shot because they can't be rezzed in soon enough.  Better that than to let it rot though.<br>
<br>
6.  I also agree that we need to be patient on these raids.  We need to be sure that everyone sticks together!  Everyone has to take responsibility for this; for instance, if you're going AFK for more than a few seconds, let your party know.  That way, no one gets left behind.<br>
<br>
7.  How did the &quot;uninvited guests&quot; perform?  If they were a hindrance, perhaps you should consider not allowing &quot;walk-ons&quot; in the future.<br>
<br>
I want to thank BBSCo for giving me the opportunity to come along on my first dragon raid.  I hope that there will be many more such opportunities.<br>
<br>
Sanmaren Emong - Legends of Westwood <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub47.ezboard.com/uxevwulf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xevwulf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#330000>(9/27/02 6:53:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub47.ezboard.com/fblackburrowstoutco13800frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Naggy Raid</span><hr size=1> I whole heartedly regret that I couldnt help last night when we needed the ports......OMG....I froze up....restarted....no good....I DESPERATELY kept tryin to log in....for more than an Hour..I knew we needed to get the necro there....but couldnt get logged in.....I am very sorry <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
