<br>
Rowlf, we totally understand. I know that patches always cause problems for you and knew that more than likely you couldn't make it back.  We know you tried everything possible to get back online.<br>
<br>
Gnipgnop, yes, there was impatience last night and I know that some people got rather abrupt in their replies.  There was also total frustration due to the fact that VI screwed up the patch and so many of us kept going LD.   Regarding maps, it is strongly urged that one be printed beforehand.  However, I understand that printers can be down, maps can get misplaced, etc.  We try to move out as one group. Some people fall behind and they need to let the raid leader(s) know IMMEDIATELY via a tell when this happens.  I was staying on top of all the people saying they were lost, fell in lava, etc.  I had tells going out to multiple the whole raid making sure we were together, that those that inadvertantly fell in the lava and died got rez'd, etc.  I stayed on top of everything, I promise you that!<br>
<br>
I was also frustrated that I couldn't heal during the Naggy fight.  My men were falling fast and it kept saying they were LD when they got feared and my heals would not hit them. I did a petition because I had not seen the LD before when I did a previous Naggy raid and the guide said that that was correct; when feared, they should say LD.  I think we should have been closer to the action too.  The LoH's did not work because of the fear/LD.<br>
<br>
We had 5 full groups and one group with 3 others.  I do not know how many 52 we had, I do not have my list of peeps with me.<br>
<br>
Sanmaren, I do not know what happened with the boss giant.  That must have been one of the times I crashed and had to reboot.  <br>
<br>
I believe there were only 2 &quot;uninvited&quot; guests and one of them performed very well.  The other needs to learn how to raid better and know his role.<br>
<br>
I also agree that nodrop loot needs to be handled as quickly as possible so that it does not rot.  If people are LD, afk, etc, I believe it us up to the Raid Lead to pick the appropriate person if the issue gets confused.  <br>
<br>
Buffing overall went well though there seemed to be some confusion on junk buffs.  I'll continue working out the buffing plan to see if we can work out all the kinks.<br>
<br>
It will be a LOT easier to keep everyone in communication when chat channels are fixed. I learned last night how much I rely on the channels now and HATE the old way of communicating.<br>
<br>
I am up for trying Naggy again tonight if anyone is interested.  I'll log in as soon as I get home to see how many are online and if we can pull the ranks together.  Please invite your friends and guildmates and we'll show Naggy the true meaning of pain.  Be sure to bring as much resist gear as you can to help get those resists higher.<br>
<br>
Please continue posting feedback here.  As Pow said, we need the information!!  Please feel free to comment on my role in the raid as well as co-raid lead if you have comments.  I'm tough and can take it. <br>
<br>
Avallyn/Budderz<br>
