</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub47.ezboard.com/unambic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nambic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#330000>(9/27/02 9:03:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub47.ezboard.com/fblackburrowstoutco13800frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Naggy Raid</span><hr size=1> I was there as Emmuar lvl 52 wizard. I did not get feared but only got off about 4 spells before being killed. Right at the end there it did not seem like we had a big enough force on Naggy, maybe it was just my vantage point, I went to his left side to be within melee range to make sure my spells would stick.<br>
<br>
For me the frustration was due to many lockups that caused delays. This made the raid run long and that is reallty hard for our EST attendies. These lockups were really bad for me during the corpse retrival process. I would like to thank all that hung in there and got our corpses out. Thanks Guys. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub47.ezboard.com/bblackburrowstoutco13800.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=mjolner>Mjolner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#330000>(9/27/02 9:12:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub47.ezboard.com/fblackburrowstoutco13800frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Naggy Raid</span><hr size=1> Well it was a lot of fun, even if I want to hunt down some Sony/Verant QA engineers and get Medieval on their butts <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   One tactic I have heard used, that we did not use was having a group of casters locked onto two or three Melee's going after Naggy and having them firing off cancel magic everytime fear lands.  Since Naggy dispells the crap buffs we loaded first, Fear will appear in the first buff slot.  Thus cancel magic will wipe fear out as it gets is the first one in the list.  While supposedly changes have not made this 100% true anymore, I suspect that it is still a valid tactic and would allow us to keep a bunch of Melees going after Naggy all at once and might limit the amount of Fearing.  Since Paladins with deepwater gauntlets can do this for 0 mana cost, they might be a good second wave, able to help keep fear at bay on the first wave and then able to whack Naggy when the other casters are ready to join the attack.  One other tactic that I have heard of being used against Vox, and this might work for Naggy is to chain stun.  Yes its true that Stuns do not affect Naggy or the giants, however with Vox, it keeps her from casting Complete heal on herself.  As such, it might well limit the number of times that naggy is able to cast fear.<br>
<br>
Mjolner Hammerofthor<br>
52 Paladin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub47.ezboard.com/bblackburrowstoutco13800.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=mjolner>Mjolner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#330000>(9/27/02 9:25:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub47.ezboard.com/fblackburrowstoutco13800frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Naggy Results</span><hr size=1> Rowlf, we all know that you would never desert us in our hour of need.  Maybe in our minute of misery <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> , but never when you know that we need you.  I froze up 4 times as MJ and twice as Agamemnonrik, once while trying to zone and once for a few minutes when trying to enter the world.  Only think I could do was Alt-Tab to Windows and force a restart.  I sure do hope that Verant has fixed this with that patch last night.<br>
