I had a great time last night.  It's great that we can do these things that I have waited so long to do. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub47.ezboard.com/uaruga.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aruga</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#330000>(9/27/02 10:20:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub47.ezboard.com/fblackburrowstoutco13800frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LoW Response</span><hr size=1> HO Thar,<br>
<br>
Some stuff I saw from Aruga's perspective:<br>
<br>
I will take the hit for not better organizing the cleric buffs while Budderz was LD, I think what we can do next time is predesignate a 'cleric' buff  leader, that leader would get all the level info from the other clerics and set them up in such a manner so that a couple junk buffs get thrown on, then the good cleric buffs.  This could be done by setting the clerics in a line, such as when the player comes tot he cleric group he goes to Aruga first, for the first cleric buff, then to Budderz for the second cleric buff, then to  San for the 3rd buff, etc.  That way we wouldn't have folks asking if they got all their buffs.  I think this would help us on the buffing part.  Perhaps if we had a good roster of what clerics are going to attend, then Aruga or the whoever is the 'cleric leader' could set up that part of the  buffing circle.<br>
<br>
